### CSS Comments

Comments explain your code and are ignored by the browser.

---

### Syntax

```css
/* This is a comment */
```

Everything between `/*` and `*/` is ignored.

---

### Single Line Comments

```css
/* Set background color */
body {
  background-color: lightblue;
}

/* Center headings */
h1 {
  text-align: center;
}
```

---

### Multi-Line Comments

```css
/*
  This is a multi-line comment.
  It can span multiple lines.
  Useful for documenting sections.
*/

/* Header Styles */
header {
  background: #333;
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Main Content */
main {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

---

### Commenting Out Code

Temporarily disable CSS rules:

```css
h1 {
  color: blue;
  /* font-size: 24px; */  /* Disabled */
  text-align: center;
}
```

---

> **Best Practice:** Use comments to explain **why** something is styled a certain way, not **what** the code does. The code itself shows the what.

codeExample:
/* === Typography === */

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

h1 {
  color: navy;
  font-size: 2em;
  /* text-decoration: underline; */ /* Disabled */
}

/* === Layout === */

.container {
  max-width: 960px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
